Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
set_pulse_clock_max_width(25.10)              set_pulse_clock_max_width(25.10)

Name
       set_pulse_clock_max_width  -  Sets  the  maximum pulse clock width con-
       straint on the specified pulse generator cells, pulse generator library
       cells, clocks, and/or current design

Syntax
       set_pulse_clock_max_width

       <pulse_width>

       <object_list>

       [-transitive_fanout]

       Sets the maximum pulse clock width constraint on  the  specified  pulse
       generator  cells, pulse generator library cells, clocks, and/or current
       design.

       To report the maximum pulse clock width constraint, you can use the re-
       port_constraint -check_type pulse_clock_max_width command.

Parameters
       <object_list>
              Specifies a list of objects - pulse generator cells, pulse  gen-
              erator library cells, clocks, or current design.

       <pulse_width>
              Specifies the pulse width value.

       -transitive_fanout
              Specifies the pulse width value for transitive fanout.

Examples
       The  following example sets the max pulse clock width constraint of 1ns
       on the pulse generator instance 'pg_inst':

       set_pulse_clock_max_width 1 pg_inst

       This constraint can be observed using the following command:

       report_constraint pg_inst/Y -check_type pulse_clock_max_width

       Fragmented output:

       --------------------------------------------

       Pin Required Actual Pulse Slack Clock Type

       Pulse Width Width

       --------------------------------------------

       pg_inst/Y (high) 1.000 0.366 0.634 PG

       --------------------------------------------

